---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Canopy from '../components/Canopy.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Colophon — Alfred Birkelund"
  description="Privacy, corrections, and contact."
>
  <Canopy />
  <article class="essay reading">
    <header class="essay__header">
      <h1 class="essay__title">Colophon</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="essay__body">
      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        No cookies set by this site, no analytics, no tracking pixels.
        Fonts are self-hosted, so rendering a page doesn't send any
        request to Google or a third-party CDN.
      </p>
      <p>Two third parties enter the picture when you use the site:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Cloudflare Turnstile</strong> — an invisible bot-check
          on the subscribe form. A small script loads from
          <code>challenges.cloudflare.com</code> on the home page.
          Cloudflare states it doesn't use cookies or fingerprint
          visitors across sites; it analyzes request signals to filter
          bots. Legal basis: legitimate interest in preventing abuse.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Resend</strong> — if you submit the subscribe form,
          your email is sent to a small Cloudflare Worker which uses
          <a href="https://resend.com">Resend</a> to email you a
          confirmation link. Click the link and your address is stored
          in a Resend audience until you unsubscribe. Open- and
          click-tracking are disabled. Legal basis: your consent (the
          confirmation click).
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        GitHub, like any web host, keeps short-lived access logs (IP,
        user agent, request path) for operating the service. I don't
        have access to those logs.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm the data controller. To unsubscribe, use the link in any
        newsletter email. To request a copy of the data held about you,
        or its erasure, email
        <a href="mailto:alfredbirkelund@gmail.com">alfredbirkelund@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Corrections &amp; contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any amendments, questions, or concerns, please email me at
        <a href="mailto:alfredbirkelund@gmail.com">alfredbirkelund@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="meta">Last updated: April 2026.</p>
    </div>

    <footer class="essay__footer">
      <a href="/">← Home</a>
    </footer>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
